Nasal polyps are noncancerous growths that develop in the lining of the nose or sinuses. The global nasal polyps treatment market can be segmented based on treatment type, distribution channel, and region. In terms of treatment type, the market is categorized into steroids, antibiotics, immunomodulators, monoclonal antibodies, and surgery. Steroids are commonly prescribed for reducing inflammation, while antibiotics are used to treat any underlying infections. Immunomodulators work by regulating the immune response, and monoclonal antibodies target specific proteins involved in the development of nasal polyps. Surgery is usually considered when other treatments fail to provide relief. The distribution channels for nasal polyps treatment include hospitals, clinics, retail pharmacies, and online pharmacies. Geographically, the market is analyzed across North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, Latin America, and the Middle East & Africa.

